      "media": [],
      "retweet": null,
      "quoted": {
        "id": "2040435591121178927",
        "text": "Here’s Ben Stein in 1979 describing television as an engine of cultural demoralization. He argues that a small clique of producers and writers pushed a left-coded inversion of reality onto the public. They despised traditional power centers and hated figures like Buckley. They propagandized the nation into accepting a fake world where businessmen are villains, criminals are the good-guys, small towns are sinister, military officers are proto-fascists, and work barely exists.",
        "created_at": "Sat Apr 04 14:25:29 +0000 2026",
        "lang": "en",
        "media": [
